29/04/2010
MUNICH, Germany -- Police arrested on Wednesday (April 28th) a 35-year-old man suspected of June 1999 war crimes in Kosovo. He was detained at the Munich airport based on an international arrest warrant. Police refuse to release his name, but Bruno Vekaric, spokesperson for the Serbian war crimes prosecutor's office, described him as a former member of the Kosovo Liberation Army, suspected of war crimes committed against civilians in Djakovica/Gjakova. (Tanjug, RTS - 28/04/10)
